s defined, and its restriction to parabolic subgroups is determined. In Chapter 4 the author computes the character of D(V), and shows how to obtain other members of the discrete series by applying Galois automorphisms to D(V). Applications are in Chapter 5. As one of the main applications of his study the author gives a precise analysis of a Brauer lifting of the standard representation of GLn(Fq).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aAlgebraic fields. 0aLinear algebraic groups. 0aRepresentations of groups. 0aSeries. 7aMATHEMATICS / Group Theory.2bisacsh  aAddition.  aAffine group.  aAutomorphism.  aDimension.  aEigenvalues and eigenvectors.  aEndomorphism.  aField of fractions.  aFinite field.  aFree module.  aGrothendieck group.  aHomomorphism.  aLinear subspace.  aMorphism.  aP-adic number.  aPartially ordered set.  aSimplicial complex.  aTensor product.  aTheorem.  aWitt vector.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Annals of Mathematics eBook-Package 1940-2020z9783110494914oZDB-23-PMB08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140088176540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400881765423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781400881765/original  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-PMBc1940d2020